## Your interview answer

> "The key architectural decisions: First, fan-out via Kafka — one raw notification event goes to a Router that publishes to channel-specific topics. This decouples channels so an SMS outage doesn't block emails. Second, idempotency at ingestion — Redis setIfAbsent with the idempotency key prevents duplicate sends even when upstream services retry. Third, retry with DLQ — DefaultErrorHandler with exponential backoff retries 3 times, then moves to a dead letter topic for manual inspection or later replay. Fourth, dual-store delivery status — Redis for fast real-time lookups, PostgreSQL for permanent audit trail. At 10M/day that's 116/sec which Kafka handles easily; the main engineering work is in reliability — dedup, retry, and DLQ."

