**Layer 2 — Per-user rate limiting** (prevents volume abuse):
```java
@Service
public class NotificationRateLimitService {

    private final RedisTemplate<String, String> redis;

    public boolean isAllowed(String userId, String notifType) {
        // Allow max 10 emails per user per hour
        String key = "notif:ratelimit:" + userId + ":" + notifType + ":" + hourBucket();
        Long count = redis.opsForValue().increment(key);
        redis.expire(key, 1, TimeUnit.HOURS);

        if (count == 1) return true;       // first in this hour window
        if (count <= 10) return true;      // within limit
        log.warn("Rate limit exceeded for user {} type {}: {} in 1h", userId, notifType, count);
        return false;                      // blocked
    }

    private String hourBucket() {
        return String.valueOf(Instant.now().getEpochSecond() / 3600);
    }
}
```

